    "recap_headline": "University of Toledo",
    "recap_text": "MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. \u2013 The Toledo baseball team dropped the middle game of a three-game series to Central Michigan, falling 18-7 in eight innings at Keilitz Field on Saturday.\nThe Rockets (10-10, 6-2 MAC) pushed in front, 2-1 in the third inning, but the Chippewas (8-11, 2-6 MAC) scored in each of the third, fourth, fifth and sixth innings to go ahead, 8-2. Toledo responded with four runs in the top of the seventh to get within two, 8-6. However, CMU opened up the game with five tallies in the bottom of the seventh and forced the run rule with five more in the eighth.\nThe top four of the Rockets' order \u2013\nCade Baker\n,\nCharlie Scholvin\n,\nTroy Sudbrook\nand\nAlex McCranie\neach supplied two-hit games. Baker scored two runs while McCranie led with two RBIs.\nStarter\nDeron Swanson\n(2-3) took the loss.\nToledo and Central Michigan will decide the series on Sunday. First pitch is at 1:00 p.m.\nQuoting Head Coach\nRob Reinstetle\n\"Not what I expected at all when we walked into the park today. For as well as we've played over the past couple of weeks through yesterday, today was just a bad day all around. We didn't pitch it at all, our defense wasn't great and we came up short on offense. We were in this position last week \u2013 play well and easily win on Friday, lose on Saturday and need to win on Sunday to take the series.\"\nTop Rocket Hitters\nCade Baker\n\u2013 2-for-4, 1 RBI, 2 runs, 1 2B, 1 HBP\nCharlie Scholvin\n\u2013 2-for-4, 1 RBI, 1 run, 1 HBP\nTroy Sudbrook\n\u2013 2-for-4, 1 RBI, 1 run, 1 2B, 1 BB\nAlex McCranie\n\u2013 2-for-4, 2 RBIs, 1 sac fly\nPitching Lines\nDeron Swanson\n(L, 2-3) \u2013 5.0 IP, 10 H, 5 R, 3 ER, 0 BB, 2 Ks\nHow it Happened\nA triple followed by an RBI single gave CMU a 1-0 lead in the first inning.\nToledo loaded the bases in the top of the third, with consecutive sac flies by\nAlex McCranie\nand\nLuke Walton\nputting Toledo in front, 2-1.\nThe Chippewas reclaimed the lead in the bottom of the third, 3-2 on a pair of two-out RBI singles.\nA sacrifice fly in the fourth and another two-out RBI single in the fifth extended the CMU advantage to 5-2.\nCentral Michigan scored three more in the sixth on an RBI single and a two-run double.\nToledo climbed within 8-6 with a four-run seventh. After two hit by pitches led off the inning,\nCade Baker\ndropped in an RBI double, and\nTroy Sudbrook\nand\nAlex McCranie\neach brought home a run with an RBI single. Another run came home on an error by the pitcher.\nThe Chippewas responded with five runs in the bottom of the seventh inning to take their biggest lead at 13-6. Three of the runs came on a bases-clearing double with one out.\nHarrison Bowman ended the game in the eighth with a grand slam.",
